news.title: Mumbai Metro train trials to start by early 2022
news.para: The state government has permitted the MMRCL to create a temporary facility - a train delivery and testing track area for the technical trials of the prototype 8-coach trains due to arrive here by December, said MMRCL Managing Director Ranjit Singh Deol.

news.title: Rajasthan CM to launch special campaign to resolve issues of people
news.para: The opening day will record a ceremonious procession with a band, where five families will be issued lease deeds at chief minister Ashok Gehlot’s residence, after they reach there from Bais Godam Circle.

news.title: About 80 families stay put in Jewar villages over rehabilitation demands
news.para: About 450 families still have certain issues that remain unresolved, of which 70 to 80 families are staying put at their native villages without power and water connections.

news.title: Buy land for the rehabilitation of 159 Mahadalit families: HC to Bihar government
news.para: A high-level committee had decided on February 20, 2019 that each of the 159 families should be given four-decimal land for rehabilitation. The land has to be purchased by the revenue and land reforms department.

news.title: Jaipur commissioner says give exemption in UD and house tax to maximum people
news.para: Commissioner Yagya Mitra Singhdeo has directed all the zone deputy commissioners and revenue officers to give the benefit of exemption given by the government in house tax and UD tax to maximum number of people.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation to conduct special camps to regularise unapproved layouts
news.para: All the housing plots in the layouts can be regularised if the owner of one of the housing plots had got a sold out plot framework (SPF) from the town planning department of the corporation.

news.title: One-time settlement scheme for defaulting Yamuna Expressway plot allottees
news.para: The Yamuna Expressway Authority has set up a portal to handle the end-to-end process online. Officials say the OTS scheme launched from Friday is expected to generate a positive response this time as YEIDA has decided to waive off the compounded penal amount in entirety and will only levy simple interest.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to launch land pattas distribution today
news.para: The government had already made arrangements to distribute these pattas, where integrated survey was already conducted. The integrated survey includes physical identification of the property, fixation of its boundaries and issuance of permanent pattas.

news.title: Bajaj Housing Finance cuts home loan Interest rate
news.para: Eligible applicants can transfer the balance amount on their home loan to Bajaj Housing Finance Limited and avail of the reduced interest rate.

news.title: People rush to Bikaner archives to get land records issued by erstwhile rulers
news.para: The RSAB has 20 lakh digital land records and has opened a special kiosk to provide copies of the documents to the potential beneficiaries.

news.title: CIDCO offers four plots to women's groups in Navi Mumbai
news.para: Two of these plots are in Nerul area while other two are in Ulwe and Dronagiri, the City and Industrial Development Corporation said in a release here.

news.title: Birla Corp shareholders approve management supported resolutions at AGM
news.para: In a statement late in the evening, PPTCL, one of the largest investment companies of the MP Birla Group, alleged "illegal and fraudulent" actions at the AGM of Birla Corporation Ltd (BCL) by the management and said it is exploring legal recourse against its chairman and directors.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC 'approves' land deal for Bhendi Bazaar redevelopment project
news.para: As part of the deal, BMC will hand over 24 plots within the redevelopment zone and will get two plots in return in Bhuleshwar and Mandi in South Mumbai.

news.title: HSBC, Yes Bank cut home loan rates
news.para: Yes Bank too has announced a limited period a offer on, ‘Yes Premier Home Loans’ at 6.7%. It gives extra 0.05% benefit (interest rate at 6.65%) for prospective salaried women homebuyers.

news.title: Grasim Industries gets Rs 8,334-crore income tax demand
news.para: The company said it would "take appropriate action against the said Order which it believes is against the spirit of tax laws." Earlier, the DCIT had sought dividend distribution tax for the same deal in 2019, which was stayed by the Bombay High Court.
